<p>Imagine you&rsquo;re on a quest to understand the very nature of computation. You&rsquo;re deep in the wilderness, far from any paths, and inscrutable messages are carved into the trunks of trees all around you &mdash; BPP, AC0, &Sigma;2P, YACC, and hundreds of others. The glyphs are trying to tell you something, but where to begin? You can&rsquo;t even keep them all straight. Few researchers have done as much as Russell...</p>
